name: Delhi Darbar Candolim Goa - Original Branch

reviews.review_text: We visited from UK tonight and was served by Jayanta Kar and he was very professional and friendly. He provided great service. The food was amazing. Huge portions, so make sure you skip lunch as we were unable to eat it all. Would definitely recommend. Thank you!

Amazing butter chicken, tandoori chicken, Kali miri chicken and naan - we order home delivery from here often and love the food.
Upon dining in also, the food is very good but the sizzling brownie is absolutely horrible and the kulfi is weak. Avoid desserts here. The service is good, but ambiance is very noisy with loud music. .

It was great dining experience. Food was very very delicious and Jayanta gave us fast and best service. I appreciate him. If you are looking for great food and great service in North Goa around Candolim must choose Delhi Darbar

description:
## Experience the Best of Indian Cuisine at Delhi Darbar Candolim, Goa

Nestled in the vibrant neighborhood of Candolim, Goa, **Delhi Darbar** stands out with an impressive rating of **4.8** from an enthusiastic crowd of **4,457** reviewers. Recognized for its fantastic **cooperative service**, pleasant demeanor, and lush **natural ambiance**, this restaurant attracts patrons not only for its delectable dishes but also for the professional yet friendly service that elevates the dining experience.

### Ambiance & Design

As you step into Delhi Darbar, you’re welcomed by a warm and inviting atmosphere that perfectly combines traditional Indian aesthetics with modern flair. The restaurant features elegant decor that reflects the rich culinary heritage of India. Soft lighting casts a cozy glow over tastefully arranged tables, creating an ideal setting for both family gatherings and intimate dinners. However, some guests have noted that the ambiance can get quite lively, with music that occasionally amplifies the energy within the space, catering to an upbeat dining experience.

![Ambiance](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdnLvCezPlSiF38M23kPZGPOMPYLVjqpH6d8EyOdia3JN-j9qbCGZUAjP9mc6LfWNIsAgPcdvLlzAI9yS1q1TmwRvZtDrbPwg7-VVICHPdA9ZOii9mAHEy5gdR92L4oNeoQoHTv7=w750-h563-p)

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Delhi Darbar is particularly known for its **butter chicken**, **tandoori chicken**, and **Kali miri chicken**, delectable options that keep both locals and tourists coming back for more. The generous portion sizes are often highlighted in reviews, with patrons suggesting diners skip lunch to savor every bite of their meals. One enthusiastic visitor from the UK lauded the food as "amazing," emphasizing the satisfying experience that accompanies each dish. The naan, a staple in North Indian cuisine, is reportedly a must-try alongside these culinary treasures. 

However, it’s worth noting that while the main dishes receive high praise, the **desserts** do not quite meet the same standards. Patrons have found the **sizzling brownie** uninspired and the **kulfi** lacking in flavor, prompting some to skip dessert altogether.

![Dishes](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdlea6DJlSaZdcpwGv_U9Ny-UGQ52BCjaNUBslBaceye3QWvL4lQ40050z0yGlDUcWEx2neO27js924FAl1Gfl3ikfUJP641_QOtg-ezt-2_KjLlkWUL2nrlpLWz_SvfCy0jkTQ=w375-h563-p)

### Customer Experience & Service

Highlighting the exemplary service, many reviews sing praise for staff members such as **Jayanta Kar**, who is described as both **professional** and **friendly**. Customers appreciate the attentive and quick service that enhances their dining experience, ensuring that their needs are met efficiently. The restaurant also appears to be accommodating, as it caters to both reservation and walk-in guests, making it easy for customers to enjoy a meal at their convenience.

### Popularity & Reviews

Delhi Darbar has captivated its audience, leading to a significant social media buzz that mirrors the sentiments expressed in customer reviews. People are consistently recommending this restaurant for its top-notch Indian cuisine and impressive service, cementing its status as a must-visit dining destination in North Goa. While occasional feedback points to the loud music detracting from the overall experience, the general consensus is overwhelmingly positive.

### Conclusion

With its delicious menu, upbeat ambiance, and commendable service, **Delhi Darbar Candolim** is undeniably a food lover’s paradise in Goa. Whether you are a local or a visitor from afar, this restaurant promises an enthralling culinary journey that celebrates the richness of Indian flavors. Just remember to save room for those hearty main courses while considering the desserts. Embrace the experience of dining at Delhi Darbar—where every detail is crafted to leave a lasting impression.
